               <birth notBefore="1430" notAfter="1435" cert="low"> He was born at <placeName ref="LOC5922Tatya">Ṭaṭyā</placeName> probably between <date>1430-35</date>.</birth>
                  <residence/>
                 
               <floruit notBefore="1400" notAfter="1500"> He was a 15th century monk and saint who is considered to be the founder of  
                  the monastery of <placeName ref="LOC2935EndaSe">ʾƎndā Śǝllāse</placeName>. 
                  He received his monastic garb at the monastery of <placeName ref="LOC2251DabraB">Dabra Bizan</placeName> 
                  by <roleName type="title">ʾabbā </roleName> <persName ref="PRS7820Petros">Ṗeṭros</persName>. 
                  Then, he went to <placeName ref="INS0105DD">Dabra Dammo ʾAbuna ʾAragāwi</placeName> for further education. 
                  Up on its completion, he moved back to <placeName ref="LOC2991Eritre">Eritrea</placeName> and established himself  
                  at <placeName ref="LOC4103Kodadu">Kodādu</placeName>. Finally, he founded the monastery of <placeName ref="LOC2935EndaSe">
                     ʾƎndā Śǝllāse</placeName> at a place called <placeName ref="LOC5369Robra">Robrā</placeName>. 
                  He was succeeded by <persName ref="PRS2392Bakwera">Bakwǝra Dǝngǝl</persName>. </floruit>
